Pydantic AI is a Python agent framework designed to help you quickly, confidently, and painlessly build production grade applications and workflows with Generative AI.
FastAPI revolutionized web development by offering an innovative and ergonomic design, built on the foundation of Pydantic Validation and modern Python features like type hints.

For more follow this link -> https://pydantic.dev/docs/ai/overview/

Pre-Requesite ->

      Software Requirements
            Python 3.10 or later (PydanticAI and the Groq SDK require Python 3.10+)
            Visual Studio Code (recommended)
            pip (Python package manager)
            Git (optional, for version control)
     
      Required Python Libraries
            pip install pydantic-ai
            pip install requests
            pip install python-dotenv

      API Keys Required
            GROQ_API_KEY
            OPENWEATHER_API_KEY
      
      Environment Variables(Storing secrets)
            GROQ_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
            OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx


# we are creating here an agent which will tell us about the weather according to cities.
# we are using here pydantic ai as agent framework
# also groq as an LLM model 


# here I am using an AI agent which will use a weather tool for getting the relative answers as per user query.

# the weather_agent() is the function which contains the model information.

# get_weather_forecast() is the function which is used as a weather tool.

# the weather tool we created is using openweathermap api docs which is providing all the weather details for specific city.

# the GenAI\Pydantic_AI\agent.py is the main file were we are creating both the agents and weather tool .


Flow 

User Question
      │
      ▼
weather_agent.run_sync(question)
      │
      ▼
1. Sends the question to the LLM
      │
      ▼
2. LLM reads the system prompt
      │
      ▼
3. LLM decides it needs the
   get_weather_forecast() tool
      │
      ▼
4. PydanticAI calls your Python function
      │
      ▼
5. Function calls OpenWeather API
      │
      ▼
6. Function returns WeatherForecast
      │
      ▼
7. PydanticAI sends the tool result
   back to the LLM
      │
      ▼
8. LLM writes the final answer
      │
      ▼
9. Returns the final result object
